		<description><![CDATA[Three weeks ago I launched my first contest to win one of two pairs of tickets to the Art of Marketing Conference in Montreal. The conference on September 30th features Seth Godin, Jeffrey Gitomer, Avinash Kaushik, Mitch Joel, Max Lenderman and Andy Nulman giving you big things to think about in marketing. The winners of [...]]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a href="http://www.theartofmarketing.ca/" target="_blank"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-1099" title="theartof-marketing-micro" src="http://www.adelemcalear.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/theartof-marketing-micro.jpg" alt="" width="260" height="112" /></a>Three weeks ago I launched my first <a href="http://www.adelemcalear.com/2010/09/01/win-tickets-to-the-art-of-marketing/" target="_blank">contest to win one of two pairs of tickets</a> to the <a href="http://www.theartofmarketing.ca/" target="_blank">Art of Marketing</a> Conference in Montreal. The conference on September 30th features <a href="http://sethgodin.typepad.com/" target="_blank">Seth Godin</a>, <a href="http://www.gitomer.com/" target="_blank">Jeffrey Gitomer</a>, <a href="http://www.kaushik.net/avinash/" target="_blank">Avinash Kaushik</a>, <a href="http://www.twistimage.com/blog/" target="_blank">Mitch Joel</a>, <a href="http://www.experiencethemessage.com/" target="_blank">Max Lenderman</a> and <a href="http://www.andynulman.com/" target="_blank">Andy Nulman</a> giving you big things to think about in marketing.</p>
<p>The winners of my Art of Marketing contest are:</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong><a href="http://www.emelineandannabelle.com/" target="_blank">Annabelle Agnew</a></strong><br />
(<a href="http://twitter.com/sewlounge" target="_blank">@sewlounge</a>)</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong><a href="http://www.jamestaylor.ws/" target="_blank">James Taylor</a></strong><br />
(<a href="http://twitter.com/JumboJet04" target="_blank">@JumboJet04</a>)</p>
<p style="text-align: left;">Congratulations!</p>
<p style="text-align: left;">Thanks to everyone who took the time to enter and tell me about what they hoped to learn by 2011 and what they&#8217;ve learned in 2010. I&#8217;ll be doing a follow up post that will take a look at those answers.</p>
<h3 style="text-align: left;">STILL TIME TO GET DISCOUNT &amp; LINCHPIN</h3>
<p style="text-align: left;">My readers can use <strong>discount code AM26</strong> when ordering to save:</p>
<ul>
<li> $50 per ticket on 1 or 2 tickets</li>
<li>$100 per ticket on orders of 3 or more</li>
</ul>
<p>You&#8217;ll get a free copy of Seth Godin&#8217;s Linchpin if you are one of the first 10 people to use the discount code.</p>
<p>Thanks to <a href="http://www.theartofproductions.com/" target="_blank">The Art of Productions</a> for sponsoring this contest.</p>
<p><em><br />
</em></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">
<p><strong>Methodology:</strong></p>
<p>As I knew several of the entrants, I used a list randomizer from <a href="http://random.org" target="_blank">Random.org </a>to make the selection fair and impartial. I randomized two lists, <a href="http://img.skitch.com/20100922-cpnsa2fbdh5e4w77qengb7kat4.jpg" target="_blank">one for women</a> and <a href="http://img.skitch.com/20100922-q3d2pwbmg91mykn9h85qrwpssr.jpg" target="_blank">one for men</a>, for equal representation at the conference.</p>
<p><em>Disclosure: I have been provided with two tickets for the Art of Marketing conference in exchange for this promotion.</em></p>
