			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>This second installment of my love of infographics is dedicated to design.</p>
<p>Two design inspired infographics for today:</p>
<ul>
<li> If you&#8217;ve ever been responsible for creating a company logo, you understand how critical colour is to your process. Colours convey different ideas, emotions and positioning before a single line is drawn. This infoinfographic on the <strong>colours of top 100 sites in the world </strong>is both eye candy and insightful.</li>
<li>My Twitter buddy <a href="http://twitter.com/duanebrown" target="_blank">@duanebrown</a> has launched a cool new design blog and shop called <a href="http://tinycelestial.com/" target="_blank">Tiny Celestial</a>. It was there that I found t his great infographic on <strong>design fantasy camp</strong>.</li>
</ul>
<h3>The Colors of the Web</h3>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://static.colourlovers.com.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/images/top-web-brand-colors.html" target="_blank"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1199" title="most-powerful-web-colors" src="http://www.adelemcalear.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/most-powerful-web-colors.jpg" alt="" width="500" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: left;"><a href="http://static.colourlovers.com.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/images/top-web-brand-colors.html" target="_blank"></a>See the original and background information on <a href="http://www.colourlovers.com/business/blog/2010/09/15/the-most-powerful-colors-in-the-world" target="_blank">ColourLovers.com</a>. The post also includes Wired&#8217;s infographic from 10 years ago on the colours of corporate America and another from this year looking at the colours of the top 1 million sites&#8217; favicons.</p>
